Often we have a need to move a parent and all of its children to another space. This happens when someone develops content in one place that should be in another space, but they didn't know...or, we end up breaking one space into a couple because it gets too large and doesn't stay focused.  Finally, we like to develop drafts in one location that only a few have access to and then move them to the open space for public consumption.  We cannot create them in the space they need to be in because we run into conflicts with the same page names as we are often working on major changes to existing pages, but don't want to update them until the 1) feature is implemented 2) the content is done and approved. 

We have a similar need on deletion.  We want to be able to delete a page and its children when we are doing our wiki gardening and the information is no longer relevant.  Or, we have to delete the old doc before moving in the new doc because of the unique name requirement as mentioned above.

